      <!--
        O4 "Energy" — backmost card, tucked behind O3 (O3's real card only spans to local
        x468.97 = design x1527.15, so O4's own right ~191px sits past that and is never
        covered by anything). Title 1:15825 "Energy" (real text, 50.89px, navy) — its OWN
        bbox width (170px) exactly matches just this one word, confirming the FULL title
        really is the single word "Energy", not a truncation (brief's "…nergy" fragment
        fully resolved). Header: the visible fragment was "…TED, / H-STAGE CAPITAL"
        (node 1:15827's clip mask). get_design_context on the card flattens this to an
        already-clipped raster image (same as the visible fragment — no better than the
        composite), so recovered it the same way as the O2/O3 chips: downloaded the RAW
        content asset behind the mask directly and rendered it standalone. Its own viewBox
        (0 0 236.29×38.84 — much wider than the ~76px visible remainder) contains the FULL
        two-line header: "AFFILIATED, GROWTH-STAGE CAPITAL".
        Fix round 1 — O4's header LAYOUT is also unique in the source: the label content
        (1:15831, canvas x1356.1-1592.4 from its own inset percentages, cross-checked
        against the mask-position offset 1418.55-62.4 = 1356.15) starts 56.2px LEFT of
        O4's own card border (x1412.28) and there is no numeral beside it — the label
        occupies the numeral's usual spot and hangs out under O3. Its right end (card-
