<style>
  .programs {
    background: var(--color-cream);
    /* Canvas fill sampled directly (1:15780, the page's own background vector) is
       #F2F1E9 — 1-2 units off `--color-cream` (#F3F2EB) in every channel, within this
       file's usual Illustrator-import rounding noise (not a deliberate distinct shade).
       Hero.astro/HowItWorks.astro both already paint their own section backgrounds as
       `--color-cream` rather than this raw sample, so this section matches its neighbors
       instead of introducing a barely-perceptible seam. */
    overflow-x: hidden; /* contains the O1 spark's small left bleed, see .o1-spark below */
    /* Gap from HowItWorks' chevron bottom (1:16816, y2086.17) to this row's own top
       (y2239.64) is 153.47px; HowItWorks already contributes 6rem/96px of that via its
       own padding-bottom, leaving 57.47px (3.59rem) here. Task 6 whole-page fidelity pass
       confirmed this renders correctly (153.4375px measured at 1024/1366/1920 alike) —
       no change needed.
       padding-bottom (6rem) confirmed too: this row's own bottom (all four O-cards share
       height 606.86px on shared top y2239.91 → bottom 2846.77) to CTA's H2 top
       (1:16268, y2978.28) is 131.51px design vs 131.5px rendered at all three gate
       widths — verified correct as-is. */
    padding-top: 3.59rem;
    padding-bottom: 6rem;
  }

  .programs-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start; /* all four cards share one top y in the design — no bottom-alignment waterfall needed here, unlike HowItWorks/Pillars */
  }

  .card {
    position: relative;
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    box-sizing: border-box;
    border: 0.125rem solid var(--color-ink-alt); /* 2px navy default; O1 overrides to orange below */
    background: var(--color-cream);
    min-height: 37.93rem; /* 606.86px, shared by all four cards' own frames (606.86-607.13px jitter) */
    /* The corner-flag notch as a REAL cutout (see cornerFlag() frontmatter comment for
       the full evidence that it's a window, not a drawing). This polygon removes the
       top-right notch from the card — background, border corner and any content crossing
       it (e.g. O4's source-positioned header label) all clip at the cut, and the card
       behind shows through the void, which is what makes the rear numerals/header
       fragments visible exactly as in the composite.
       --cut/--cut-end hold the design's own cut offsets (114.62px/95.55px from each
       card's right edge) as PERCENTAGES of each card's own design width (values in the
       per-card rules below) rather than fixed px: the cards are %-of-row columns that
       compress with the viewport, and a fixed-px notch on a shrinking card ate a growing
       share of it (39% of O3 at 1024 vs the design's 24%), pushing the cards' own header
       labels through their own notch. As percentages the notch compresses in lockstep
       with its card, so every text-vs-notch relationship measured at 1920 holds across
       the desktop range (fonts scale with vw, cards with row %, both ~linear in
       viewport). At 1920 the percentages reproduce the design px exactly.
       Boundary = the redrawn stroke's OUTER edge (design centerline +1px outward,
       small-angle approximation; stub edge 87.07 = 88.07-1). The overlay stroke in
       .card-flag below is centered 1px inside this line, so the clip leaves it intact
       (the fixed 1px offset vs the scaled geometry drifts sub-pixel, ~0.4px at 1024 —
       absorbed by anti-aliasing). The -80px/+2px outer points keep everything else
       unclipped, including O1's spark overhanging at -67.68px and both borders. */
    --cut: 114.62px; /* fallback (also restored <1024 where cards are full-width) */
    --cut-end: 95.55px;
    clip-path: polygon(
      -80px -2px,
      calc(100% - var(--cut) + 1px) -2px,
      calc(100% - var(--cut-end) + 1px) 87.07px,
      calc(100% + 2px) 87.07px,
      calc(100% + 2px) calc(100% + 2px),
      -80px calc(100% + 2px)
    );
  }
  /* Per-card notch percentages: 114.62px and 95.55px over each card's own design width
     (572.54 / 533.12 / 468.97 / 305.72 — the flag offsets are constant px in the design,
     so the narrower the card, the larger its notch share). */
  .card--o1 {
    width: 37.47%; /* 572.54 / 1527.85px row span, see frontmatter */
    z-index: 4;
    border-color: #f37d2c;
    --cut: 20.02%; /* 114.62 / 572.54 */
    --cut-end: 16.689%; /* 95.55 / 572.54 */
  }
  .card--o2 {
    width: 34.9%; /* 533.12 / 1527.85px */
    z-index: 3;
    margin-left: -8.05%; /* 123.01px overlap with O1 */
    --cut: 21.5%; /* 114.62 / 533.12 */
    --cut-end: 17.923%; /* 95.55 / 533.12 */
  }
  .card--o3 {
    width: 30.69%; /* 468.97 / 1527.85px — O3's own real card width, not the group's inflated bbox */
    z-index: 2;
    margin-left: -7.5%; /* 114.62px overlap with O2 */
    --cut: 24.441%; /* 114.62 / 468.97 */
    --cut-end: 20.374%; /* 95.55 / 468.97 */
  }
  .card--o4 {
    width: 20.01%; /* 305.72 / 1527.85px */
    z-index: 1;
    margin-left: -7.52%; /* 114.87px overlap with O3's real (not group) right edge */
    --cut: 37.492%; /* 114.62 / 305.72 */
    --cut-end: 31.254%; /* 95.55 / 305.72 */
  }

  /* Corner-flag stroke overlay (see cornerFlag() frontmatter comment for the cutout
     construction). Fixed px, anchored to the card's own top-right corner regardless of
     the card's fluid width — the notch's offsets-from-right-edge are constant in the
     design regardless of card width, so % sizing would wrongly stretch it. Absolute
     children position against the PADDING box, so -0.125rem (the border width) puts the
     svg's top/right edges on the border-box's own outer edges — giving the svg-local ↔
     border-box mapping the frontmatter comment derives. */
  .card :global(.card-flag) {
    position: absolute;
    top: -0.125rem;
    right: -0.125rem;
    width: calc(var(--cut) + 1px); /* the card's own notch % + the 1px centerline inset — x-stretches the viewBox by the same factor as the clip polygon, see frontmatter */
    height: 5.6294rem; /* 90.07px, fixed: card heights don't scale, only widths do */
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  /* O1's decorative spark (see frontmatter comment) — positioned so its own right edge
     (where the sparkle sits, per the raw SVG's own local x68.5-81.79 hot zone) lands
     beside the "O1" numeral, matching the screenshot; left of that trails the thin
     flourish line, bleeding slightly past the card's own left border (contained by
     `.programs`'s own overflow-x:hidden above). */
  .card--o1 .o1-spark {
    position: absolute;
    left: -4.23rem; /* 67.68px — group 1:16449's own left inset ahead of the card border (1:16453 at x122.47 vs card at x190.15) */
    top: 4.04rem; /* 64.62px — 1:16453's own y (2304.44) minus card top (2239.64) */
    width: 10.25rem; /* 164px */
    height: 3.4375rem; /* 55px */
  }

  .card-head {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center; /* numeral and 2-line label share one visual center (2285.99 vs 2284.67px, ~1px apart) */
    gap: 1.26rem; /* 20.12px, O1's own numeral-to-label gap (293.9 to 314.02) */
    padding: 0.5531rem 2.36rem 0; /* 8.85px top — O1's own card-top-to-numeral-top gap */
    /* 66.43px = 8.85px padding + the numeral's design line box (57.58px). Pinning the
